解答题.15:
1) ∵ sinA + \sqrt{3}cosA = 2
   ∴ 2(\frac{1}{2}sinA + \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}cosA) = 2
   ∴ sin(A + \frac{\pi}{3}) = 1
   ∵ A ∈ (0, π)
   ∴ A + \frac{\pi}{3} = \frac{\pi}{2}
   ∴ A = \frac{\pi}{6}

2) ∵ \sqrt{2}bsinC = csin2B
   ∴ \sqrt{2}bsinC = 2csinBcosB
   ∴ cosB = \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}
   ∴ B = \frac{\pi}{4}

   ∴ b = \frac{a}{sinA} \cdot sinB = 2\sqrt{2}

   sinC = sin(\pi - A - B) = sin(A + B) = sin(\frac{\pi}{6} + \frac{\pi}{4}) = \frac{\sqrt{6} + \sqrt{2}}{4}

   c = \frac{a}{sinA} \cdot sinC = 4 \cdot sinC = \sqrt{6} + \sqrt{2}

   ∴ 周长 = a + b + c = 2 + \sqrt{6} + \sqrt{2} + 2\sqrt{2} = 2 + \sqrt{6} + 3\sqrt{2}
